What is Electric Circuits?

Electric circuits are the basic building blocks of modern electronics. They are made up of a series of conductors and resistors. The conductive elements are called "electrons" and the resistive element is called a "conductor".
.
The basic components of an electronic circuit are:
1. An electrical conductor (electron)
